itment to transparency and good governance to help scale these solutions. Responsibilities: Support DIGI with thorough research and writing, stay on top of digital advancements in the field of governance and social impact; Â  Monitor events and research of peer organizations and leaders in the field as well as preparing for meetings and vetting project proposals; Help us create content and update the program\u2019s website and social media accounts; Help organize and staff online discussions, round-tables, and other public or invite-only events. Learning Outcomes: Gain familiarity with the use of technology for better governance and social impact applications; Better understand the internal operations of a non-profit organization; Gain leadership experience while helping us manage and monitor pilot projects; Acquire social media tricks of the trade, while building an online presence; Develop relationship building skills, event/project management skills while interacting with our partners and advisory board. Â Internship Stipend College credit or Paid Â Qualifications: Qualifications students must have to apply for the internship: Outstanding organization, follow up, and multitasking abilities; The ability to engage credibly with a broad range of high-level partners from foundations, civil society, the private sector, and government; Â Excellent research, writing, and communication skills; An interest in emerging technologies; An ability to work and solve problems on an independent, entrepreneurial basis with a high degree of autonomy; Â  Social media aptitude and/or experience. Â Application Process: To apply, please submit a resume and cover letter. Â Submissions will be considered on a rolling basis. No phone calls, emails or letters please. New America is an equal opportunity employer committed to hiring a diverse workforce at all levels of the organization thereby creating a culture that allows us to better serve our mission, our employees, and our communities. 